		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One sure think is that to have acess to the connector, you HAVE TO break six little pins of plastics that covers it, and so doing that would technically "do irreversible damage to the console".
<br />My SNES have a very similar unused connector, but this time it is user-accessible.

		

		</td>
