	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The connector is covered by a break-off piece of plastic, which in turn is covered by a plastic door that snaps shut. If you break off the plastic but keep the door snapped on when you don't have anything connected to the expansion port, nobody will know nor care that you have used the expansion port.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


